TITLE: Advanced usage with useVideoPlayer hook in React
DESCRIPTION: Example demonstrating how to use the useVideoPlayer hook for more control over the MuxPlayer component. This approach allows direct access to the props needed for customizing the video player implementation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/datocms/react-datocms/blob/master/docs/video-player.md#2025-04-17_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { useVideoPlayer } from 'react-datocms';

const data = {
  muxPlaybackId: 'ip028MAXF026dU900bKiyNDttjonw7A1dFY',
  title: 'Title',
  width: 1080,
  height: 1920,
  blurUpThumb:
    'data:image/bmp;base64,Qk0eAAAAAAAAABoAAAAMAAAAAQABAAEAGAAAAP8A',
};

// `props` is the following object:
//
//     {
//        playbackId: 'ip028MAXF026dU900bKiyNDttjonw7A1dFY',
//        title: 'Title',
//        style: {
//          aspectRatio: '1080 / 1920',
//        },
//        placeholder:
//          'data:image/bmp;base64,Qk0eAAAAAAAAABoAAAAMAAAAAQABAAEAGAAAAP8A',
//      }
const props = useVideoPlayer({ data });

<MuxPlayer {...props} />
```

